{
  "texts": [
    "The deployment of smart contracts, characterised by their self-executing nature and encoded execution of predefined rules, also introduces privacy risks.",
    "The contents of these contracts, accessible to all parties on the blockchain, can jeopardise the privacy of individuals participating in legal transactions (Staples et al. 2017).",
    "See Fig. 2.",
    "Beyond the realm of privacy, the integration of blockchain into legal systems necessitates a comprehensive evaluation of data security.",
    "Blockchain's reputation for security is rooted in cryptographic mechanisms and decentralisation."
  ]
}